 # Data Analysis & Machine Learning Practice
## Overview
This repository contains exploratory data analysis (EDA) and machine learning (ML) practice projects using publicly available datasets. Each dataset folder includes the raw data, a structured analysis workflow, and clear documentation. The goal is to build strong, end‑to‑end data science skills through hands‑on practice.

##Repository Structure
Each dataset is organized in its own folder:
Dataset-Name/
    README.md
    data.csv
    eda.ipynb
    ml_model.ipynb   (optional)


This structure keeps the work modular and easy to navigate.

##Typical Workflow
Every dataset follows a consistent analysis pipeline:
1. Data Understanding
- Review column definitions
- Identify data types
- Check for missing values
- Detect inconsistencies or anomalies
2. Data Cleaning
- Handle missing values
- Fix incorrect data types
- Remove or cap outliers
- Standardize categorical values
3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Summary statistics
- Distribution plots
- Correlation analysis
- Group-wise comparisons
- Insights about patterns and trends
4. Feature Engineering (Optional)
- Create new meaningful variables
- Transform skewed features
- Encode categorical variables
5. Machine Learning (Optional)
- Train/test split
- Baseline models
- Model comparison
- Hyperparameter tuning
- Evaluation metrics (accuracy, ROC-AUC, F1, etc.)

## Goals of This Repository
- Strengthen Python and Pandas skills
- Build intuition for real-world data cleaning
- Practice visual storytelling with Matplotlib/Seaborn
- Develop ML modeling experience
- Create portfolio-ready projects for job applications

## Datasets Used
This repository may include datasets from:
- Kaggle
- UCI Machine Learning Repository
- Open-source government datasets
- Public domain CSV files
Each dataset folder contains a dataset-specific README with details and insights.

## Tools & Libraries
Typical tools used across projects:
- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Matplotlib, Seaborn
- Scikit-learn
- Jupyter Notebook

## Future Enhancements
- Add ML pipelines for more datasets
- Include model explainability (SHAP, feature importance)
- Add dashboards or interactive visualizations
- Convert selected projects into end‑to‑end case studies
